_instructions: Comprehensive evidence-based exercise database for hypertrophy and strength training. Each exercise carefully selected and classified based on biomechanics, muscle activation research, and practical effectiveness.

_fieldGuide.movementPatterns: Array. Values: horizontal_push, vertical_push, horizontal_pull, vertical_pull, squat, hinge, lunge, carry, rotation, anti_rotation, flexion, extension, abduction, adduction, isolation (only for exercises that don't fit other patterns)
_fieldGuide.splitTag: Which PPL day. Values: push, pull, legs, core, conditioning
_fieldGuide.isMainLiftEligible: Can be selected as the primary heavy lift for a session (1-6 reps, high mechanical tension)
_fieldGuide.difficulty: beginner, intermediate, or advanced - based on technique complexity and prerequisite strength
_fieldGuide.unilateral: true if exercise works one limb at a time, false if bilateral
_fieldGuide.repRangeRecommendation: Object with min and max rep recommendations for hypertrophy/strength
_fieldGuide.jointStress: low, medium, high - cumulative stress on joints and connective tissue
_fieldGuide.equipment: Array of: Barbell, Dumbbell, Machine, Cable, Bodyweight, Kettlebell, Band, Sled, Bench, Rack, EZ_Bar, Trap_Bar
_fieldGuide.fatigueCost: 1-5, systemic fatigue generated per set (CNS + metabolic + muscular)
_fieldGuide.sfrScore: 1-5, stimulus-to-fatigue ratio (5 = excellent stimulus with minimal fatigue)
_fieldGuide.lengthPositionScore: 1-5, how well it loads the muscle in a stretched/lengthened position (5 = maximal stretch under load)
_fieldGuide.stimulusBias: Array of: mechanical (heavy tension), metabolic (pump/burn), stretch (lengthened position emphasis), stability (motor control)
_fieldGuide.contraindications: Object with body part keys (knee, low_back, shoulder, elbow, wrist, hip) mapping to true, or null
_fieldGuide.primaryMuscles: Array of muscles this exercise primarily targets
_fieldGuide.secondaryMuscles: Array of muscles this exercise secondarily targets
